  "bodyHtml": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"6709\" data-permalink=\"https://parishinvestments.com/2017/11/07/the-guardian/the_guardian_logo-1/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/the_guardian_logo-1.png?fit=1020%2C348&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1020,348\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"the_guardian_logo-1\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/the_guardian_logo-1.png?fit=900%2C307&amp;ssl=1\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/the_guardian_logo-1.png?resize=428%2C146&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6709\" width=\"428\" height=\"146\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/the_guardian_logo-1.png?w=1020&amp;ssl=1 1020w, https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/the_guardian_logo-1.png?resize=300%2C102&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/the_guardian_logo-1.png?resize=768%2C262&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-rounded\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-large is-resized\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"7077\" data-permalink=\"https://parishinvestments.com/2019/02/11/the-guardian-revealed-wife-of-putins-spokesman-faces-questions-over-us-tax-affairs/lukeharding/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lukeharding.png?fit=498%2C496&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"498,496\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"lukeharding\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lukeharding.png?fit=498%2C496&amp;ssl=1\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lukeharding.png?resize=158%2C158&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7077\" width=\"158\" height=\"158\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lukeharding.png?w=498&amp;ssl=1 498w, https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lukeharding.png?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lukeharding.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lukeharding.png?resize=400%2C400&amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lukeharding.png?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 158px) 100vw, 158px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-rounded\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-large is-resized\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"6712\" data-permalink=\"https://parishinvestments.com/2017/11/07/the-guardian/index-2/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/index.jpg?fit=225%2C225&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"225,225\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"index\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/index.jpg?fit=225%2C225&amp;ssl=1\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/index.jpg?resize=158%2C158&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6712\" width=\"158\" height=\"158\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/index.jpg?w=225&amp;ssl=1 225w, https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/index.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/index.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 158px) 100vw, 158px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">By Luke Harding and Jon Swaine &#8211; February 11, 2019</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Questions have been raised about the US tax affairs of the wife of Vladimir Putin’s spokesman, after records suggested she may have failed to declare her true income to US regulators and not disclosed foreign bank accounts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Tatiana Navka,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y_11TiSYMBw\">a former Olympic ice dancing champion</a>, also appears to have wrongly claimed a potentially beneficial US tax status, according to an investigation by the Guardian.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"7081\" data-permalink=\"https://parishinvestments.com/2019/02/11/the-guardian-revealed-wife-of-putins-spokesman-faces-questions-over-us-tax-affairs/attachment/2875/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/2875.jpg?fit=620%2C372&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"620,372\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"2875\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/2875.jpg?fit=620%2C372&amp;ssl=1\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/2875.jpg?resize=515%2C309&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7081\" width=\"515\" height=\"309\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/2875.jpg?w=620&amp;ssl=1 620w, https://i0.wp.com/parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/2875.jpg?resize=300%2C180&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 515px) 100vw, 515px\" /><figcaption>Tatiana Navka, with her husband, the Russian presidential spokesman, Dmitry Peskov, attend a premiere at the Bolshoi Theatre in Moscow in 2017. (Photograph: Valery Sharifulin/Tass)</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Court papers suggest she separately built up tens of thousands of dollars in unpaid property taxes on a house she told US authorities she had already sold. Navka lived and trained in the US for more than a decade.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-coblocks-alert\"><p class=\"wp-block-coblocks-alert__text\">Bill Parish, an Oregon-based investment adviser who has worked as a tax consultant to US government investigators, said married taxpayers are treated very differently than single filers.<br><br>“There is huge amounts of law based around that,” said Parish. “Millions of ordinary taxpayers who get divorced have to go through the pain of untangling their finances to resume filing as single.”</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Note:</strong> This story was based upon original research by Parish &amp; Company.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons aligncenter is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\" href=\"https://parishinvestments.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Revealed_-wife-of-Putins-spokesman-faces-questions-over-US-tax-affairs-_-US-news-_-The-Guardian.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">View Original Article</a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"></p>\n",
  "bodyText": "By Luke Harding and Jon Swaine – February 11, 2019\n\nQuestions have been raised about the US tax affairs of the wife of Vladimir Putin’s spokesman, after records suggested she may have failed to declare her true income to US regulators and not disclosed foreign bank accounts.\n\nTatiana Navka, a former Olympic ice dancing champion, also appears to have wrongly claimed a potentially beneficial US tax status, according to an investigation by the Guardian.\n\nTatiana Navka, with her husband, the Russian presidential spokesman, Dmitry Peskov, attend a premiere at the Bolshoi Theatre in Moscow in 2017. (Photograph: Valery Sharifulin/Tass)\n\nCourt papers suggest she separately built up tens of thousands of dollars in unpaid property taxes on a house she told US authorities she had already sold. Navka lived and trained in the US for more than a decade.\n\nBill Parish, an Oregon-based investment adviser who has worked as a tax consultant to US government investigators, said married taxpayers are treated very differently than single filers.\n\n“There is huge amounts of law based around that,” said Parish. “Millions of ordinary taxpayers who get divorced have to go through the pain of untangling their finances to resume filing as single.”\n\nNote: This story was based upon original research by Parish & Company.\n\nView Original Article",
